ance":7},{"pos":"Noun","root":"አገር","word":"አገር","synonyms":["country","land","nation"],"importance":7}],"summary":"The input batch was processed through 8 scholarly protocols. Protocol 1 (The Splitter) was applied to separate clitics like 'ና' and 'ም' from their base words, and 'ንም' from 'የሒትሌርንም'. Protocol 2 (The Judge) led to a scholarly guess for 'ነረቱት', which was corrected to 'ነገሩት' (they told him) due to common OCR confusion between 'ረ' and 'ገ' and the lack of a clear root for 'ነረት'. Protocol 3 (The Corrector) addressed visual OCR confusions and normalized spellings (e.g., 'ሠ' to 'ሰ', 'ሣ' to 'ሳ', 'ፀ' to 'ጸ', 'ሃይፐርማኬት' to 'ሃይፐርማርኬት', 'ምናቃለሁ' to 'ምናውቃለሁ'). Punctuation and affixes were stripped to derive the clean word and root. Protocol 4 (The Lemmatizer) identified the infinitive or base form for all valid words. Protocol 5 (The Translator) provided comprehensive English synonyms. Protocol 6 (The Grammarian) assigned appropriate Parts of Speech. Protocol 7 (The Filter) strictly enforced the rule that 'Amharic words must be at least 2 characters long'. Consequently, single-character particles such as 'ና' (and) and 'ም' (also/even) were discarded from the final dataset, even though they are semantically meaningful clitics. The particle 'ንም' was retained as it consists of two characters. Protocol 8 (Executive Summary) reflects on these decisions, particularly the strict application of the size constraint for particles.","input_words":["እንድታጠናክርና","ሊሸማቀቅና","የማይሸረሸሩ","ካላመነኝ","አያበድረኝም","ያወራረዱበትን","እንዲያስቆርጡ","እስክትመሰርቱ","ገዳማትም","እንዳትወስዱ","ተለውጠህም","ላይነኩ","ሃይፐርማኬቱን","ምናቃለሁ","ሳታሳምም","የሚደመስስና","የሒትሌርንም","እንዲጠቀሙለት","ከሠማ","ሮህጋ","የሁባ","ወደለውጥ","መፀፀቷን","ቢያስነብብም","ለመምህራኖች","ነረቱት","ሣጥኖችም","ያቆየናቸው","እንዲነሣባቸው","ባገራቸውም"],"batch_number":null,"batch_label":null,"model_version":"gemini-2.5-flash"}]